…you know.
I wasn't built that way.

252
00:13:14.404 --> 00:13:15.655
I just…

253
00:13:16.614 --> 00:13:18.533
I feel like there's always
something inside of me

254
00:13:18.616 --> 00:13:19.617
holding me back.

255
00:13:33.006 --> 00:13:34.007
["Boy" playing]

256
00:13:45.185 --> 00:13:47.312
No. no. no.

257
00:13:47.395 --> 00:13:48.396
♪ <i>Uh-huh</i> ♪

258
00:13:49.397 --> 00:13:50.398
Come on.

259
00:13:55.111 --> 00:13:56.112
♪ <i>Uh-huh</i> ♪

260
00:13:59.074 --> 00:14:00.366
Okay. get up. bitch.

261
00:14:00.450 --> 00:14:02.368
-Get up! Come on!
-No. Oh. God.

262
00:14:02.452 --> 00:14:04.245
-[Eli] Come on!
-[Patrick] That's right.

263
00:14:04.913 --> 00:14:06.122
-[Eli] You too.
-What the fuck?

264
00:14:06.206 --> 00:14:07.499
Put that phone away
and get up.

265
00:14:07.582 --> 00:14:09.167
-Okay.
-[Eli] Get your asses up.

266
00:14:09.250 --> 00:14:11.086
-[Patrick] Come on.
-[Eli] Come on!

267
00:14:59.008 --> 00:15:00.260
Iris. what are you doing?

268
00:15:22.031 --> 00:15:23.199
[groans]

269
00:15:24.784 --> 00:15:27.078
[breathes heavily] Ah!

270
00:15:28.538 --> 00:15:29.789
[grunting]

271
00:15:41.176 --> 00:15:42.927
I'm so glad we did this.

272
00:15:44.637 --> 00:15:46.639
Being here with you
is just perfect.

273
00:15:47.891 --> 00:15:48.892
Uh-huh.

274
00:15:50.435 --> 00:15:54.439
I'm sorry if I was being weird
or mopey earlier.

275
00:15:57.609 --> 00:16:02.280
I just want you
to be happy. Josh. That's all.

276
00:16:02.363 --> 00:16:03.948
Iris. go to sleep.

277
00:16:07.410 --> 00:16:09.204
[water running]

278
00:16:20.215 --> 00:16:22.467
It's such a gorgeous day out.

279
00:16:23.468 --> 00:16:24.803
[Josh] Uh. what's the weather?

280
00:16:25.345 --> 00:16:26.930
It's currently 72 degrees

281
00:16:27.013 --> 00:16:29.682
with an 83% chance
of rain in the evening.

282
00:16:29.766 --> 00:16:31.267
[Josh chuckles]
It never gets old.

283
00:16:34.187 --> 00:16:36.564
-[water stops running]
-[spits. sighs]

284
00:16:37.649 --> 00:16:40.235
-[Iris] You almost ready?
-Oh. I'm sorry. babe.

285
00:16:40.318 --> 00:16:41.778
I think I need
some time to shower

286
00:16:41.861 --> 00:16:43.446
and pound
a few gallons of coffee.

287
00:16:43.530 --> 00:16:44.781
Why don't. uh--

288
00:16:44.864 --> 00:16:46.908
Why don't you head
down there by yourself?

289
00:16:46.991 --> 00:16:48.493
But it was your idea.

290
00:16:49.160 --> 00:16:52.163
You said you wanted a nice.
relaxing morning by the lake.

291
00:16:52.247 --> 00:16:54.999
I know. but that's before the
hangover caught up with me.

292
00:16:55.083 --> 00:16:57.335
Last night was a lot.

293
00:16:58.378 --> 00:16:59.879
You had fun though. right?

294
00:17:01.214 --> 00:17:02.841
Of course I did. Beep-Boop.

295
00:17:03.842 --> 00:17:05.176
Last night was incredible.

296
00:17:18.898 --> 00:17:20.315
You want me to wait?

297
00:17:21.442 --> 00:17:23.695
We could
make the shower for two.

298
00:17:25.989 --> 00:17:28.283
Nah. no. no.
That's okay. Um…

299
00:17:29.325 --> 00:17:30.410
You go on ahead.

300
00:17:31.286 --> 00:17:33.496
Enjoy as much of this
gorgeous day as you can.

301
00:17:35.832 --> 00:17:37.250
-Okay.
-[chuckles] Yeah.

302
00:17:37.333 --> 00:17:38.460
-Hmm.
-[sighs]

303
00:18:23.296 --> 00:18:25.048
[birds chirping]

304
00:19:11.845 --> 00:19:13.346
[Sergey speaking Russian]

305
00:19:18.101 --> 00:19:19.310
Sorry?

306
00:19:19.394 --> 00:19:20.812
Means "good morning."

307
00:19:21.771 --> 00:19:23.148
Oh. yes.

308
00:19:24.190 --> 00:19:25.650
<i>Dobroe utro</i> to you too.

309
00:19:25.734 --> 00:19:28.611
Hey. your Russian is not bad.

310
00:19:28.695 --> 00:19:32.282
It is not good.
but also it is not bad.

311
00:19:32.365 --> 00:19:33.616
[both chuckle]

312
00:19:35.243 --> 00:19:36.244
Nice view.

313
00:19:42.542 --> 00:19:43.668
[speaking Russian]

314
00:19:43.752 --> 00:19:44.836
To love.

315
00:19:46.546 --> 00:19:47.547
[Sergey slurps]

316
00:19:53.511 --> 00:19:54.596
Mmm.

317
00:19:54.679 --> 00:19:55.680
You like?

318
00:19:55.764 --> 00:19:58.183
I think I'm actually going to
head back inside.

319
00:19:59.392 --> 00:20:00.393
So soon?

320
00:20:00.477 --> 00:20:01.853
Yeah…

321
00:20:01.936 --> 00:20:03.563
Josh wasn't feeling great
this morning.

322
00:20:03.646 --> 00:20:05.023
so I think I should
check in on him.

323
00:20:05.106 --> 00:20:07.859
Josh is big boy.
He can take care of himself.

324
00:20:07.942 --> 00:20:09.861
Stay. Keep Sergey company.

325
00:20:11.488 --> 00:20:13.364
I really think I should
see him.

326
00:20:15.533 --> 00:20:16.534
You…

327
00:20:17.952 --> 00:20:19.454
like lake house. yes?

328
00:20:21.289 --> 00:20:22.290
Yeah.

329
00:20:22.373 --> 00:20:24.918
You enjoy your time here?

330
00:20:25.001 --> 00:20:27.128
Mm-hmm. Yeah. very much.

331
00:20:27.212 --> 00:20:30.965
Then as guest. please stay.

332
00:20:31.049 --> 00:20:33.384
Keep this old Russian man
company.

333
00:20:36.513 --> 00:20:38.598
-Okay.
-Wonderful.

334
00:20:38.681 --> 00:20:39.682
Mmm.

335
00:20:49.818 --> 00:20:51.820
Oh. [sniffs]

336
00:20:53.279 --> 00:20:54.280
You mind?

337
00:20:55.490 --> 00:20:57.367
Just back and shoulders.

338
00:20:57.450 --> 00:20:59.285
-It's tough to reach.
-Oh.

339
00:20:59.369 --> 00:21:01.329
Don't want to get too tan.

340
00:21:11.506 --> 00:21:12.507
[Iris] Okay.

341
00:21:15.468 --> 00:21:16.469
Mmm.

342
00:21:19.973 --> 00:21:22.016
And shoulders. please.

343
00:21:22.100 --> 00:21:23.268
Okay.

344
00:21:30.191 --> 00:21:31.192
[Sergey inhales sharply]

345
00:21:38.158 --> 00:21:39.284
What are you doing?

346
00:21:41.077 --> 00:21:44.289
It's not problem.
This Kat's idea.

347
00:21:44.831 --> 00:21:46.791
She tell Sergey
you are down here.

348
00:21:47.333 --> 00:21:48.752
Give Sergey permission.

349
00:21:50.211 --> 00:21:52.046
Let go of my hand. please.

350
00:21:52.130 --> 00:21:54.924
This is what you do. yes?

351
00:21:55.008 --> 00:21:57.635
This is what you are for.

352
00:22:00.680 --> 00:22:02.098
-[kisses] Mmm.
-Please.

353
00:22:02.849 --> 00:22:03.975
Please stop.

354
00:22:05.435 --> 00:22:06.478
[Josh chuckling]

355
00:22:06.561 --> 00:22:07.979
[Eli] I was drunk.
I mean. you--

356
00:22:08.062 --> 00:22:09.022
[Eli] Last night.
it was crazy.

357
00:22:09.105 --> 00:22:10.064
[Josh]
You were extremely drunk.

358
00:22:10.148 --> 00:22:12.066
You were drunk too.
Like. more drunk than I got.

359
00:22:12.150 --> 00:22:13.777
I don't really get drunk.
It's like this gift.

360
00:22:13.860 --> 00:22:15.695
Like. people get bloated
and stuff. and not me.

361
00:22:15.779 --> 00:22:17.822
-Like. never happens.
-Never get bloated.

362
00:22:17.906 --> 00:22:19.866
Never. It's like I could drink
and do whatever I want.

363
00:22:19.949 --> 00:22:22.077
-It's like you get dehydrated.
-Yeah. just. like--

364
00:22:22.160 --> 00:22:23.411
What the fuck?

365
00:22:24.287 --> 00:22:25.580
[Josh] Oh. shit.

366
00:22:25.663 --> 00:22:28.458
-Iris. what the fuck?
-[Iris whimpers]

367
00:22:30.418 --> 00:22:31.836
I didn't mean to. He--

368
00:22:31.920 --> 00:22:32.921
[Josh breathes heavily]

369
00:22:33.004 --> 00:22:35.048
He forced himself on me.

370
00:22:35.590 --> 00:22:36.591
Who did?

371
00:22:37.842 --> 00:22:38.843
Sergey?

372
00:22:40.011 --> 00:22:41.262
Mmm.

373
00:22:41.346 --> 00:22:42.514
Please.

374
00:22:42.597 --> 00:22:45.266
Sergey just want little taste.
[kisses]

375
00:22:48.937 --> 00:22:50.855
I just wanted him to stop.

376
00:22:52.482 --> 00:22:54.818
Oh. God. Sergey.

377
00:22:57.862 --> 00:23:01.491
Iris. Hey. look at me. Look
at me. Talk me through it.

378
00:23:01.574 --> 00:23:02.659
What happened?

379
00:23:03.410 --> 00:23:05.203
[breathes shakily] I--

380
00:23:06.413 --> 00:23:08.498
[kissing]

381
00:23:09.374 --> 00:23:10.458
I said stop!

382
00:23:14.796 --> 00:23:16.214
I didn't have a choice.

383
00:23:24.514 --> 00:23:25.598
Sergey?

384
00:23:27.058 --> 00:23:28.059
[groans]

385
00:23:34.607 --> 00:23:35.608
[speaking Russian]

386
00:23:36.609 --> 00:23:38.778
[Sergey grunting]

387
00:23:38.862 --> 00:23:40.905
-[grunting]
-[speaking Russian]

388
00:23:40.989 --> 00:23:44.033
He wouldn't let go.
He was choking me. Josh.

389
00:23:44.117 --> 00:23:45.535
[both grunting]

390
00:23:45.618 --> 00:23:46.745
[speaking Russian]

391
00:23:47.912 --> 00:23:49.164
And then I--

392
00:23:49.247 --> 00:23:50.749
And then you what. Iris?
Then you what?

393
00:23:50.832 --> 00:23:52.041
[both grunting]

394
00:23:55.003 --> 00:23:55.962
[Sergey grunting]

395
00:23:56.045 --> 00:23:57.088
[Iris]
<i>He was trying to kill me.</i>

396
00:23:57.172 --> 00:23:58.298
<i>and the only thing
I could think about</i>

397
00:23:58.381 --> 00:23:59.466
was that if he did kill me.

398
00:23:59.549 --> 00:24:01.050
I'd never get to
see you again.

399
00:24:01.134 --> 00:24:03.762
and that hurt so much more
than the pain of being choked!

400
00:24:03.845 --> 00:24:05.305
I wouldn't let that happen.

401
00:24:05.388 --> 00:24:06.681
I couldn't let him take me
away from you.

402
00:24:06.765 --> 00:24:08.683
I love you so much!

403
00:24:08.767 --> 00:24:10.059
Iris. go to sleep.

404
00:24:16.024 --> 00:24:18.234
[Iris humming]

405
00:24:21.529 --> 00:24:23.281
[Josh. muffled] Okay.
Don't forget her ankles. okay?

406
00:24:23.782 --> 00:24:24.949
[Patrick. muffled] Okay.

407
00:24:25.033 --> 00:24:26.451
Are you sure
this is gonna hold?

408
00:24:26.534 --> 00:24:27.994
[Josh. normal]
Yeah. no. it's fine.

409
00:24:28.078 --> 00:24:29.454
She's not superhuman
or anything.

410
00:24:29.537 --> 00:24:31.664
She's only as strong
as they want her to be.

411
00:24:41.758 --> 00:24:43.009
[Josh sighs]

412
00:24:46.054 --> 00:24:47.055
[sighs]

413
00:24:54.437 --> 00:24:55.647
Handcuff knot.

414
00:24:58.566 --> 00:25:00.402
-Hey.
-Hey.

415
00:25:00.485 --> 00:25:01.736
[Josh] How's she doing?

416
00:25:01.820 --> 00:25:04.155
She's asleep.
I gave her two Xanax.

417
00:25:04.239 --> 00:25:06.449
Xanaxes? Xani?

418
00:25:06.533 --> 00:25:08.827
-Whatever. she's asleep.
-Okay. good. Good.

419
00:25:08.910 --> 00:25:10.370
[sighs] So…

420
00:25:11.871 --> 00:25:12.872
what do we do now?

421
00:25:12.956 --> 00:25:14.749
Uh. I mean.
the only thing we can do.

422
00:25:14.833 --> 00:25:17.127
We call the cops.
We tell them everything.

423
00:25:17.210 --> 00:25:18.336
Right. yeah.

424
00:25:18.420 --> 00:25:20.422
-Yeah.
-But what about…

425
00:25:21.756 --> 00:25:25.468
Well. uh. obviously
I'll need to. uh. you know.

426
00:25:26.678 --> 00:25:28.388
I just don't understand
how this could have happened.

427
00:25:28.471 --> 00:25:30.056
Don't they have safeguards
for this kind of shit?

428
00:25:30.140 --> 00:25:31.391
I have no idea.

429
00:25:31.933 --> 00:25:33.768
Like a glitch maybe?

430
00:25:34.519 --> 00:25:35.603
Yeah.

431
00:25:37.897 --> 00:25:40.775
Okay. Okay. so…

432
00:25:42.193 --> 00:25:44.070
I'll call the cops.
and you will…

433
00:25:44.154 --> 00:25:46.030
-Yeah. Yeah.
-Yeah. Yeah.

434
00:25:46.114 --> 00:25:48.992
Sorry. do you mind.
um. taking it outside?

435
00:25:49.075 --> 00:25:52.579
Just 'cause…
I-- I wanna say goodbye.

436
00:25:54.831 --> 00:25:55.832
Yeah.

437
00:25:55.915 --> 00:25:57.542
-Yeah. buddy. Sure.
-Yeah. thanks.

438
00:26:07.635 --> 00:26:08.803
Iris. wake up.

439
00:26:08.887 --> 00:26:09.888
…be lost without you!

440
00:26:09.971 --> 00:26:12.515
Hey. hey. hey.
Hey. it's okay. You're okay.

441
00:26:12.599 --> 00:26:14.642
-You're okay. I'm here. Hey.
-[breathing shakily] Josh.

442
00:26:14.726 --> 00:26:16.227
-Listen to me.
-[breathing shakily]

443
00:26:16.311 --> 00:26:19.606
Wait. Why are my hands tied?
Why are my hands tied. Josh?

444
00:26:19.689 --> 00:26:21.983
Iris. We didn't have a choice.
We didn't have a choice.

445
00:26:22.066 --> 00:26:23.777
You murdered Sergey.
You remember?

446
00:26:23.860 --> 00:26:24.694
No. no. no. no.

447
00:26:24.778 --> 00:26:26.446
It was self-defense.
He was gonna kill me.

448
00:26:26.529 --> 00:26:28.490
He was gonna kill me.
You gotta believe me.

449
00:26:28.573 --> 00:26:30.075
No. I believe you. Iris.

450
00:26:30.158 --> 00:26:31.910
I mean. you couldn't lie to me
even if you wanted to.

451
00:26:32.619 --> 00:26:33.620
What?

452
00:26:33.703 --> 00:26:37.082
It's. um.
part of your programming.

453
00:26:37.957 --> 00:26:40.460
Programming? What the hell
are you talking about?

454
00:26:41.002 --> 00:26:42.003
[Iris breathes shakily]

455
00:26:42.087 --> 00:26:43.463
Okay. um…

456
00:26:43.546 --> 00:26:45.882
Sorry. there's just
no delicate way to say this.

457
00:26:45.965 --> 00:26:49.969
So. I'm just gonna
rip the Band-Aid right off.

458
00:26:50.053 --> 00:26:51.888
[Iris breathing shakily]

459
00:26:51.971 --> 00:26:53.306
You're a robot.

460
00:26:56.518 --> 00:26:57.519
I'm…

461
00:26:57.602 --> 00:26:58.895
A robot.

462
00:27:00.563 --> 00:27:05.110
More specifically.
you're a companion robot.

463
00:27:06.361 --> 00:27:08.988
A companion robot?

464
00:27:09.072 --> 00:27:10.907
Yeah. it's like a. um…

465
00:27:11.866 --> 00:27:14.619
[sighs]
I hate the word "fuckbot."

466
00:27:14.702 --> 00:27:17.414
Um. 'cause you do so much more
than that. but. uh…

467
00:27:18.706 --> 00:27:21.251
You're an
emotional support robot…

468
00:27:22.585 --> 00:27:23.753
that fucks.

469
00:27:25.505 --> 00:27:26.589
You're joking. right?

470
00:27:26.673 --> 00:27:28.591
-This is just a sick--
-Iris. what's the weather?

471
00:27:28.675 --> 00:27:29.676
It's currently 72 degrees

472
00:27:29.759 --> 00:27:32.095
with an 83% chance
of rain in the evening.

473
00:27:36.349 --> 00:27:37.183
-Are--
-Hmm.

474
00:27:37.267 --> 00:27:39.018
Are you still not convinced?

475
00:27:39.102 --> 00:27:40.728
Yeah. okay. uh…

476
00:27:41.980 --> 00:27:43.022
Let's see.

477
00:27:43.106 --> 00:27:44.858
Iris. do you know
any foreign languages?

478
00:27:44.941 --> 00:27:47.360
Can you speak. say. Spanish?

479
00:27:47.444 --> 00:27:49.863
Josh. you know
<i>no sé hablar español</i>.

480
00:27:51.406 --> 00:27:52.407
<i>¿Qué?</i>

481
00:27:52.490 --> 00:27:54.242
-How about Chinese?
-[speaking Spanish]

482
00:27:54.325 --> 00:27:56.411
[speaking Mandarin]

483
00:27:56.494 --> 00:27:57.579
Do I need to keep going?

484
00:27:57.662 --> 00:27:59.080
'Cause I can go. uh…

485
00:27:59.164 --> 00:28:01.416
I can do Portuguese.
I can do Korean.

486
00:28:01.499 --> 00:28:02.667
I can do. uh…

487
00:28:03.752 --> 00:28:06.254
I don't know what Telugu is.
but apparently you speak it.

488
00:28:06.337 --> 00:28:08.131
I don't-- I don't understand.

489
00:28:08.673 --> 00:28:09.841
I--

490
00:28:09.924 --> 00:28:11.301
No. no. no. I have memories.

491
00:28:11.384 --> 00:28:14.846
Uh. uh… College.
Uh. summer jobs. I've--

492
00:28:14.929 --> 00:28:17.307
I've been to Japan. Twice.

493
00:28:17.390 --> 00:28:18.683
Okay. so what those are--

494
00:28:18.767 --> 00:28:19.768
Those are. um…

495
00:28:19.851 --> 00:28:22.187
They're like outlines
of memories.

496
00:28:22.270 --> 00:28:25.774
You know. just enough to give
you a little. uh. backstory.

497
00:28:25.857 --> 00:28:27.984
The-- The-- The day we met
in the grocery store.

498
00:28:28.068 --> 00:28:31.654
You and the oranges. That is
not an outline of a memory.

499
00:28:31.738 --> 00:28:33.531
Yeah. it's fake.
Never happened.

500
00:28:33.615 --> 00:28:34.616
I just randomly picked it

501
00:28:34.699 --> 00:28:36.034
from a drop-down list
of meet-cutes.

502
00:28:36.117 --> 00:28:38.745
It could've been anywhere.
It could've been dog park.

503
00:28:38.828 --> 00:28:41.915
a bookstore. farmer's market.

504
00:28:44.000 --> 00:28:45.293
It never happened?

505
00:28:46.419 --> 00:28:47.962
[sighs] Okay. do. um--

506
00:28:48.046 --> 00:28:50.882
Do you wanna know how we met?
Like. how we really met?

507
00:28:52.133 --> 00:28:53.635
["Iris" playing on speakers]

508
00:28:56.429 --> 00:28:58.223
Hey. Josh Beeman?

509
00:28:58.765 --> 00:29:00.558
-Yeah. that's me.
-Okay.

510
00:29:00.642 --> 00:29:02.060
-Yeah. come on in.
